00:03:27.870 --> 00:03:29.480
ALAN STEWART: Band
keratopathy.

00:03:29.480 --> 00:03:30.950
BRADY HARAN: Band keratopathy.

00:03:30.950 --> 00:03:32.360
There we go.

00:03:32.360 --> 00:03:36.220
So now, let's find out
a bit about you.

00:03:36.220 --> 00:03:39.300
You have a sort of a sciency
background or a mathematicky

00:03:39.300 --> 00:03:39.610
background?

00:03:39.610 --> 00:03:39.920
Talk to us.

00:03:39.920 --> 00:03:41.090
ALAN STEWART: Yes.

00:03:41.090 --> 00:03:45.370
I did a degree in physics at the
University of Southampton.

00:03:45.370 --> 00:03:49.970
And I got my master's
there in 2008.

00:03:49.970 --> 00:03:54.640
My musical background is
kind of nonexistent.

00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:59.412
I had a piano lessons for two
years when I was a teenager.

00:03:59.412 --> 00:04:04.350
Well, because of my eyesight, I
never learned to read music.

00:04:04.350 --> 00:04:07.040
I can't physically see
the music to read it.

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:11.540
So that kind of limited
what I could do.

00:04:11.540 --> 00:04:12.655
So I stopped having lessons.

00:04:12.655 --> 00:04:16.039
But I continued to play and just
kind of taught myself.

00:04:16.039 --> 00:04:17.079
BRADY HARAN: So you've
taught yourself.

00:04:17.079 --> 00:04:18.850
