And I thought, it's got
to be based on pi.

00:28:41.760 --> 00:28:44.600
Because if it's not
based on pi, then

00:28:44.600 --> 00:28:46.470
what's the point, really?

00:28:46.470 --> 00:28:52.380
So I sent you some just very
light piano music with a

00:28:52.380 --> 00:28:53.470
classical feel.

00:28:53.470 --> 00:28:56.160
It was very backgroundy, very
similar to the "Spaghetti

00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:57.520
Numbers" music.

00:28:57.520 --> 00:28:59.513
BRADY HARAN: Well, let's
play that now, because

00:28:59.513 --> 00:29:00.155
I still have that.

00:29:00.155 --> 00:29:02.768
Let's play what Alan
first sent.

00:29:02.768 --> 00:29:31.700
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:29:31.700 --> 00:29:32.980
ALAN STEWART: You
weren't unhappy.

00:29:32.980 --> 00:29:35.210
You said it was nice.

