00:32:12.360 --> 00:32:13.850
number onto a scale.

00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:16.820
And with Fibonacci, we were
putting the numbers of the

00:32:16.820 --> 00:32:20.810
Fibonacci sequence on to the
notes of the C major scale,

00:32:20.810 --> 00:32:21.279
these ones.

00:32:21.279 --> 00:32:25.031
[NOTES PLAYING]

00:32:25.031 --> 00:32:25.969
BRADY HARAN: OK.

00:32:25.969 --> 00:32:27.845
Yeah.

00:32:27.845 --> 00:32:33.000
ALAN STEWART: So just to be
different, just to be

00:32:33.000 --> 00:32:37.630
outrageous, I thought, let's
